    • getString

      public String getString(String key)
      Gets the message with the given key.

      The message will be obtained either from the core ResourceBundle or a ResourceBundle of an add-on (depending on the prefix of the key).

      Note: Since 2.8.0 this method no longer throws a MissingResourceException if the key does not exist, instead it logs an error and returns the key itself. This avoids breaking ZAP when a resource message is accidentally missing. Use containsKey(String) instead to know if a message exists or not.

      Parameters:
      key - the key.
      Returns:
      the message.
      See Also:
      • getString(String, Object...)
      • getMessageBundle(String)

    • getChar

      public char getChar(String key)
      Returns the specified char from the language file. As these are typically used for mnemonics the 'null' char is returned if the key is not defined
      Parameters:

      Returns:
      the char read, or null char if not found

    • setLocale

      public void setLocale(Locale locale)
      Sets the current locale to the given one and gets a resource bundle for new locale.

      The call to this method has no effect if the given locale is the same as the current one.

      Parameters:
      locale - the new locale

    • getString

      public String getString(String key, Object... params)
      Gets the message with the given key, formatted with the given parameters.

      The message will be obtained either from the core ResourceBundle or a ResourceBundle of an add-on (depending on the prefix of the key) and then formatted.

      Note: This method does not throw a MissingResourceException if the key does not exist, instead it logs an error and returns the key itself. This avoids breaking ZAP when a resource message is accidentally missing. Use containsKey(String) instead to know if a message exists or not.

      Parameters:
      key - the key.
      params - the parameters to format the message.
      Returns:
      the message formatted.
      See Also:
      • getString(String)
